<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-21T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="603" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">819.74/261: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzalez</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-21T19:00:00-05:00">November 21, 1933—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>105. Your telegram No. 160, November 13, 4 p.m. After consultation with
                            Navy Department no objection perceived to your making informal
                            inquiries.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>